docs.snippet: PUNTA DEL ESTE, Uruguay, Jan. 26. The United States will invoke a section of its foreign aid legislation to cancel most of is remaining trade with Cuba, United States sources said here today. A dispatch printed in The New York Times today said the...
docs.lead_paragraph: PUNTA DEL ESTE, Uruguay, Jan. 26. The United States will invoke a section of its foreign aid legislation to cancel most of is remaining trade with Cuba, United States sources said here today. A dispatch printed in The New York Times today said the trade would be curbed under the Trading with the Enemy Act.
docs.abstract: US to invoke a section of its foreign aid legis to cut off all trade

headline.main: U.S. TO USE AID LAW TO CURB CUBA TRADE
